\f0\fs24 \cf0 For my project, I utilized Google Forms as the primary platform to build a "Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz." This tool was selected for its intuitive interface, which allows for the seamless integration of various question types, including multiple-choice, short-answer, and checkboxes. By leveraging its built-in data validation and real-time response tracking, I was able to construct a structured assessment that effectively measures a peer group's understanding of online safety, data privacy, and source verification.\
Building this quiz provided hands-on practice in digital content curation and instructional design. I focused on creating scenarios\'97such as identifying phishing emails and understanding "incognito" limitations\'97that reflect real-world digital challenges.\
Moving forward, mastering these tools will be highly beneficial for my academic career. Google Forms and similar data-collection platforms are essential for conducting primary research and surveys for future thesis work or group projects. Additionally, the practice of distilling complex technical concepts into clear, concise questions enhances my communication skills. These digital competencies ensure that I can effectively collaborate in a cloud-based environment and critically evaluate information, which is a cornerstone of modern academic excellence.}